, United Kingdom","Norton Lees, Derbyshire, England":"Norton Lees, Derbyshire, England","Chesterfield, Derbyshire, England":"Chesterfield, Derbyshire, England, United Kingdom","Kennoway, Fife, Scotland":"Kennoway, Fife, Scotland","Kennoway, Fife, Scotland, United Kingdom":"Kennoway, Fife, Scotland, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"McCall","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Irish and Scottish:","Anglicized form of <b>Mac Cathail</b> ‘son of <i>Cathal</i>’, a personal name meaning ‘powerful in battle’. See   Cahill  .","more rarely an Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Mac Cathmhaoil</b> ‘son of <i>Cathmhaol</i>’, a personal name composed of the elements <i>cath</i> ‘battle’ + <i>maol</i> ‘chief’. See   Cowell  ."],"variants":[{"name":"McAll","meanings":["Irish: variant of   McCall   1."]},{"name":"Cahill","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Irish Brendan, Liam, Donal, Conor, Eamon, Kieran, Ronan, Aidan, Aileen, Brigid, Colm, James Patrick.","Irish: Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Mac Cathail</b> or <b>Ó Cathail</b> ‘son (or descendant) of <i>Cathal</i>’, a personal name meaning ‘powerful in battle’."]},{"name":"McCaul","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Irish Cormac, Colm, Conor.","Irish: variant of   McCall  ."]},{"name":"McCahill","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Irish Brendan, Liam, Padraic.","Irish (northern): Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Mac Cathail</b>, an Ulster name. See   McCall  ."]},{"name":"McKeel","meanings":["Irish: perhaps an Anglicized form of Gaelic<b>Mac Cathmhaoil</b> (see   McCall  )."]},{"name":"McKale","meanings":["Scottish: variant of   McCall   1."]}]},{"name":"Sarah","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Biblical name, borne by the wife of Abraham and mother of Isaac. According to the Book of Genesis, she was originally called <i>Sarai</i> (possibly meaning ‘contentious’ in Hebrew), but had her name changed by God to the more auspicious <i>Sarah</i> ‘princess’ in token of a greater blessing (Genesis 17:15, ‘And God said unto Abraham, As for Sarai thy wife, thou shalt not call her name Sarai, but Sarah shall her name be’). This has been one of the most enduringly popular girls' names."],"variants":[{"name":"Sara","meanings":["Variant of   Sarah .  This is the form used in the Greek of the New Testament (Hebrews 11:11)."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Sarah McCall was born in 1385, in Kennoway, Fife, Scotland. She married Sir John Blythe in 1409, in Whittlesey, Cambridgeshire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 2 sons. She died in Chesterfield, Derbyshire, England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"1385–":"1385–Surnud","1380–1451":"1380–1451","1410–1480":"1410–1480","1415–1458":"1415–1458","1385–Female":"1385–Surnud","1415":"1415","1458":"1458","1410":"1410","1385":"1385","1451":"1451","1409":"1409","1480":"1480","1380":"1380","Whittlesey, Cambridgeshire, England":"Whittlesey, Cambridgeshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Norton Lees, Derbyshire, England":"Norton Lees, Derbyshire, England","Chesterfield, Derbyshire, England":"Chesterfield, Derbyshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Kennoway, Fife, Scotland":"Kennoway, Fife, Scotland","Kennoway, Fife, Scotland, United Kingdom":"Kennoway, Fife, Šotimaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1385–":"1385–Kuollut","1380–1451":"1380–1451","1410–1480":"1410–1480","1415–1458":"1415–1458","1385–Female":"1385–Kuollut","1415":"1415","1458":"1458","1410":"1410","1385":"1385","1451":"1451","1409":"1409","1480":"1480","1380":"1380","Whittlesey, Cambridgeshire, England":"Whittlesey, Cambridgeshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Norton Lees, Derbyshire, England":"Norton Lees, Derbyshire, England","Chesterfield, Derbyshire, England":"Chesterfield, Derbyshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Kennoway, Fife, Scotland":"Kennoway, Fife, Scotland","Kennoway, Fife, Scotland, United Kingdom":"Kenno